<item>
            <title>[HBASE-5590] Add more server mode state to jmx output.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-5590</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Related to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-5325&quot; title=&quot;Expose basic information about the master-status through jmx beans &quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-5325&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-5325&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-5533&quot; title=&quot;Add more metrics to HBase&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-5533&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-5533&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; there is more state information that would be good to expose in a machine readable fashion.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Some suggestions for state information include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;the balancer is on or off.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;if a master is active or a backup.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;If a we are in hlog recovery mode&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&quot;tasks&quot; distributed from distributed log splitting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;More suggestions are welcome.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
